1 olive oil
3 potato
1 bag baby broccoli
1 carrot
40 g butter
2 tbs milk
1 packet chicken breast
½ sachet Sweet Mustard Spice Blend
½ bottle cream
1 clove garlic
1 packet Grated Parmesan Cheese

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a large saucepan with
boiling water, then add a generous pinch of salt.
• Peel potato and cut into large chunks.
• Cook potato in the boiling water, over high heat,
until easily pierced with a fork, 10-15 minutes.

TIP: Save time and get more fibre by leaving the
potato unpeeled.

Little cooks: Older kids can help peel the potato
under adult supervision.

• While the potato is cooking, halve any thick baby
broccoli stalks lengthways. Thinly slice carrot
into half-moons.
• When the potatoes have 8 minutes remaining,
place a colander or steamer basket on top of the
pan, then add baby broccoli and carrot.
• Cover with a lid and steam until veggies are
tender and potatoes can be easily pierced with
a fork, 7-8 minutes. Transfer baby broccoli and
carrot to a bowl. Season, cover to keep warm
and set aside.
• Drain potatoes and return to the saucepan. Add
the butter, milk and a generous pinch of salt.
Mash until smooth. Cover to keep warm.

Little cooks: Get those muscles working and help
mash the potatoes!

• Meanwhile, finely chop garlic. Cut chicken
breast into 1cm strips.
• In a medium bowl, combine sweet mustard
spice blend (see ingredients), a drizzle of olive
oil and a pinch of pepper. Add chicken strips
and toss to coat.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil
over medium-high heat.
• When oil is hot, cook chicken strips in batches,
turning, until browned and cooked through,
3-4 minutes. Transfer to a plate.

• Wipe out the frying pan, then return to low
heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook garlic until
fragrant, 1 minute.
• Add cream (see ingredients), grated Parmesan
cheese, a splash of water and any chicken
resting juices, stirring, until thickened,
1-2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.

• Divide mash, steamed veggies and sweet
mustard chicken strips between plates.
• Spoon cheesy garlic sauce over chicken to serve.
Enjoy!